{"content":"\chapter{Introduction to Embedded Controllers}

\section{What is an Embedded Controller?}

The Embedded Controller (EC), also known as the Keyboard Controller (KBC), is the ``brain'' of the laptop's power management system. It is responsible for:

\begin{itemize}
    \item Monitoring power buttons and lid switches
    \item Controlling power rail sequencing
    \item Managing battery charging
    \item Keyboard matrix scanning
    \item Thermal management (fan control)
    \item LED indicators (caps lock, num lock, battery)
    \item Communication with the PCH (Platform Controller Hub)
\end{itemize}

\section{Real-World Example: HP EliteBook 820 G2}

\subsection{U300 - SMSC MEC1324}

In the HP EliteBook 820 G2, the Embedded Controller is:

\ic{U300}{SMSC MEC1324}{46}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Package:} TQFP-128 (128 pins, Thin Quad Flat Package)
    \item \textbf{Location:} Page 46 of schematic
    \item \textbf{Function:} Keyboard controller + power management EC
\end{itemize}

\flexbv{U300} to locate this chip on the physical board.

